37.title: Rhett Wellington Interview
37.plot: Step into the life of professional male model, Rhett Wellington. Steaming up the gram with a massive growing fan base, he's been making a great career for himself in this very competitive world. If you've ever wondered what it takes to get a big print campaign? Watch the show and learn about the industry from his point of view.

38.title: Matthew Knowles Interview
38.plot: International actor and model, Matthew Knowles sits down with Kimberly Q on The Red Booth to discuss his experience starring in the Chinese epic fantasy ASURA, the biggest film to date in China's history with a budget exceeding 100 million dollars. They cover this and much more on show.

39.title: Robert Patrick Interview
39.plot: We have the legendary Robert Patrick on this weekend. Not only is he known the world over as the T-1000 from Terminator 2, Robert has continued to have a flourishing career as a icon of our times, with major roles in hit show after hit show. But as you'll see on our show, what matters most to Robert is his love of Harley Davidson and the charity work he's been doing for 30+ years with Boozefighters MC, helping veterans and bikers alike. He's even bought his own dealership. Hear all about it on the show.

40.title: Edge of Paradise Band Interview
40.plot: Kimberly Q interviews the modern metal band Edge of Paradise. With a stunning lead singer, Margarita Monet and a band of talented rockers, any fan of rock/metal will love them. They are also one of the rock bands to hit the top Billboard 100 and for good reason. See for yourself, and watch them play live in the studio!.

43.title: Michele Martin Interview
43.plot: Michele Martin joins pinup style hostess Kimberly Q on The Red Booth this week. Michele starred in the 2010 erotic drama Assisting Venus, for which she won the LA Femme Filmmaker Award for Best Feature Producer at the 2010 LA Femme International Film Festival. She also starred in the 2011 romantic comedy Dadgum, Texas, and the 2015 dark romance, Blue. All three of which she co-wrote and produced with director Charles Huddleston. Michele has shared the screen with such greats as: Robert Patrick, Kenny Johnson, Kelly McGillis, Bruce Davison, and Heather Graham.

Get a great inside perspective on what its like to be a professional motorcycle racer and get advice from the champ himself on how you can get into racing if you so desire.

34.title: Kelly Sullivan and Medlock Krieger Special
34.plot: On this episode of The Red Booth show, we chat with Emmy nominated actress, Kelly Sullivan! You probably know her from The Young & The Restless, General Hospital and more! We talk about Kelly's new leading role in Tyler Perry's Drama and first scripted series for TLC, "Too Close to Home", also starring original Melrose Place cast member, Heather Locklear. Plus hostess Kimberly Q takes us to the red carpet for a special Rock & Roll benefit concert here in Los Angeles, The Medlock Krieger Invitational, raising money for St. Jude's Children's Research Foundation. ...

35.title: Dave Yaden Interview
35.plot: On this episode of The Red Booth, get to know singer/songwriter/musician and 4 time Grammy winner Dave Yaden! He talks about working with major artists, his new album, how he got started and more.

36.title: Jaime Zevallos Interview
36.plot: On this episode of The Red Booth, get to know Actor, Jaime Zevallos! He plays the lead bad guy in the new hit TV show Animal Kingdom TNT but he's also been in major shows like Sons of Anarchy and American Horror Story. We talk about these as well as his upcoming feature films and more.

37.title: Chris Woods Interview
37.plot: Meet musician Chris Woods. Chris has toured the US and Europe and made a lot happen already as an indie musician. He has a new album coming out this month with his new band, He-Monster and last month, he released a very special collaboration titled, "The Woods Brothers."

38.title: State to State Band Interview
38.plot: On this episode, we have the amazing indie band, State to State, they talk about their upcoming show at The Echo and their latest releases. Plus for the first time ever, they share some very exciting news about one of the biggest stars in rock history "Steve Perry" who is actually singing on two of their new songs. "Don't stop, believing" in this band because their music is truly inspiring and beautiful.

39.title: Treehouse Interview
39.plot: We have the ladies of the Treehouse Festival, Alex Wisner and Diana Mantis! They talk about the amazing growth of Tree House Events and its upcoming festival, featuring tons of local independent artists. This beautiful collaboration has been getting a lot of buzz and was even featured recently in LA Weekly and Reverb Nation!

40.title: Phil Proctor Interview
40.plot: On this episode of The Red Booth Show we have 3 time #Grammy nominated actor and comedian Phil Proctor! Of Firesign Theatre and more. He talks about his decades of experience in the biz, and the many characters he's played over the years, including hit Disney and Pixar movies like Toy Story and Finding Nemo. You have heard his voice whether you know it or not! And he's not only a voice actor but has also appeared in many TV shows and movies throughout the years. Phil even tells us (while in character) about his role in the new audio book, Battlefield Earth: A Saga of ...

41.title: Greg Travis Interview
41.plot: On this episode we have the very funny and entertaining actor, comedian and filmmaker, Greg Travis. Greg has been in some major movies including The Watchmen, Starship Troopers and many more! He did stand-up and was even the opening act for Cher! Greg has just released a long term project, his movie, Dark Seduction which he wrote and directed. The film is getting a lot of buzz not only because of the mixed genre of it, but because of the crazy story behind the making of it. A story I think a lot of filmmakers can relate to. So noteworthy that he was just featured in ...

42.title: Paul Logan Interview
42.plot: On this episode we have actor and filmmaker Paul Logan talking about his new movie The Horde which he not only starred in but also produced and wrote. It's perfect for Halloween as he battles monsters with kick ass action sequences. The movie has already garnered several accolades through festival nominations and awards for the genre. Paul also talks about how he got into acting and his time on Days of our Lives. Get to know a lot more about this very kindhearted professional actor, and what it's like to get an independent movie made!

43.title: Michelle Stafford Interview 2
43.plot: On this episode, we have the very talented Daytime Emmy winning actress and show creator Michelle Stafford! You likely know her from her current role on General Hospital or from her many seasons on The Young and the Restless! Michelle has since created a few of her own shows that showcase her hilariously entertaining flair and unabashed messages of womanhood. She shares a lot about the life of a single woman in the dating scene and becoming a mother, in her new show Single Mom A Go Go. If that isn't enough, Michelle is also the creator of an amazing new healthy skin ...

44.title: The Active Set Interview
44.plot: On this episode, we have members of The Active Set , Matthew Stolarz and Gabriel Grinta, joining us to talk about their band, their latest EP and what it was like touring the world, opening for acts like AWOLNATION, Neon Trees and more. Featured in Los Angeles Times and BuzzBands.LA Hear some great insight into their philosophy on how their band has continued to grow and their tips for other bands who want to go on tour.

45.title: Jaden LaRue Interview
45.plot: On this episode of The Red Booth Show get to know the extremely talented singer/songwriter, Jaden LaRue! Her voice is like some kind of dusky angel I'd say. But hear her for yourself and you decide. Not only does Jaden write all of her own music, but she sings, plays guitar and piano too. She has an amazing album out right now as well. Jaden also created and hosts the infamous local LA secret venue Silverlake Sessions which she tells us all about.

46.title: Ethan Suplee & Paul Adelstein Interview
46.plot: On this episode of The Red Booth, we have Ethan Suplee and Paul Adelstein from the new series "Chance" on Hulu. It's staring Hugh Laurie from "House". I watched it at first just for homework but I couldn't stop. Had to watch the whole first Season; a dark thrilling drama. I have the pleasure of talking with them both about not only their characters on Chance but also about Ethan's recent role in "Deepwater Horizon", and Paul's new "Prison Break" season returning, as well as a new scripted series on Bravo of his own creation.

47.title: Anna Camp Interview

48.title: Dominic Pace Interview
48.plot: On this episode we have actor, Dominic Pace joining us. Dominic has been in a multitude of projects, both on stage and on camera, including appearances on Desperate Housewives, NCIS, Cold Case and many more. He even has 4 new films coming out. But most notably Dominic has landed a recurring role in the new TV show Superstore. Dom talks about his philosophy on how to make it as an actor and tells us his story, as a father and family man, still making his dreams come true in this ever challenging biz.

1.title: Malcolm McDowell Interview
1.plot: This weekend on The Red Booth, we have the amazing actor Malcolm McDowell, talking about his role in Amazon's "Mozart in the Jungle" and his history going back to The Clockwork Orange.

2.title: Katheryn Winnick Interview
2.plot: This weekend on The Red Booth, we have force of nature, Katheryn Winnick, also known as the now legendary character, Lagertha, from the hit show, Vikings, on the History Channel. Get to know her surprising and rather interesting background story and what makes her so happy about playing this character. Also find out about what's to come in the new season of Vikings.

3.title: Alexa Davalos & Luke Kleintank Interview
3.plot: This weekend on the Red Booth, we have Alexa Davalos and Luke Kleintank of the Amazon Original series, The Man in the High Castle. Get to know them and more about the new season of The Man in The High Castle.

4.title: Sundance Film Festival on the Red Booth
4.plot: The Red Booth Show takes you into the 2017 Sundance Film Festival; hear from some of the filmmakers, actors and creators behind some of the festival's picks like ABC's Downward Dog, the documentary Cries from Syria, and we also take you into some pretty cool VR Lounges.

5.title: Toby Stephens Interview
5.plot: Meet the notorious Captain Flint of Black Sails, also known as Toby Stephens.. We talk about the final season of Black Sails, being a pirate, Spanish galleons and being a Dad and husband in this demanding business.

6.title: TJ Scott Interview
6.plot: This weekend on The Red Booth show we have TJ Scott. Director of TV shows like The Strain, Longmire, Gotham, Bates Motel, and more. Get to know him on the show and also hear about his new record label.

7.title: Steve Orosco MMA Interview
7.plot: This weekend on The Red Booth Show we have MMA fighter and entrepreneur Steve Orosco. Founder of Smash Global, Steve is working to change the way MMA fights are experienced and take it to the next level. He talks about his fight career and the tough times fighters face, as well as his experience in the business world which he brings to the table with this new brand of Black Tie MMA.

8.title: Jared Show Interview
8.plot: This weekend on the show, we interview filmmaker Jared Show. He is the writer, director, producer and editor of Bigfoot: The Movie, he also plays "Burl" the Exterminator in the film. Hear the story of the making of the movie and some interesting facts about BIGFOOT on this interview. The movie is out now for you to see at Walmart, Best Buy, Target and on Amazon.

9.title: Michael Dorman and Terry O'Quinn Interview
9.plot: Get to know two of the stars of the new show Patriot on Amazon Prime. Hear about their characters and fun behind the scenes stories plus advice for aspiring actors.

10.title: Rachele Royale Interview
10.plot: This weekend on The Red Booth Show, get to know singer, songwriter and performer Rachele Royale. Hand picked as one of the first artists for the new label CPG Music, Rachele has worked with some of the biggest names in Music, but has now found her home at CPG.

11.title: Richard Armitage Interview
11.plot: This weekend, we have on the show Richard Armitage, he stars on the Epix Original series "Berlin Station".

12.title: Erik Himel Interview
12.plot: Musician Erik Himel, the mastermind behind the The Sunset Jam at The Viper Room, a legendary club in Hollywood that has been home to countless music icons is our guest this week.

13.title: Red Carpet Coverage for Underground
13.plot: This week, the Red Booth takes you on the red carpet as the show covers the Season 2 of the hit show, Underground, airing on WGN America.

14.title: Dana Delany Interview
14.plot: Dana Delany, star of the Amazon Original series "Hand of God" shares with us this week about her character "Crystal Harris" on the show. We also find out about her return to the stage in a new play and we hear from Dana, as she gives her insight and advice for aspiring actors. You wont want to miss it.

15.title: David Morse Interview
15.plot:

16.title: Brett Young Interview
16.plot: We have breakout country music star, Brett Young, on the show this week.

17.title: Timbaland Interview
17.plot: This weekend on the show, we have a chat with mega music icon, Timbaland.

18.title: Moira Walley-Beckett and Amybeth McNulty Interview
18.plot: Get to know the amazing show runner Moira Walley-Beckett (Breaking Bad) and young actress Amybeth McNulty, star of "Anne with an E"; a new Netflix series depicting the original 1908 Novel "Anne of Green Gables".

19.title: Jake Busey Interview
19.plot: We have here the amazing Jake Busey. He talks about the many new shows and a new movie that he's in, including the new "The Predator" which is taking it back to the original story-line in an epic way, along with being in Ray Donovan and so much more.

20.title: Ryan Francis Interview
20.plot: Ryan J. Francis was just fourteen when he took up the role of young Peter Pan in the Academy Award nominated blockbuster "Hook" alongside Robin Williams. Directed by Steven Spielberg, this beloved roll created a lifelong legacy for Ryan, who has since gone on to star in TV shows as an adult. He talks about being a child actor and his latest projects now, as well as telling us some great stories from the set of "Hook".

21.title: George Peters Interview
21.plot: This week, we have Academy Award winner, George Peters; he's worked on mega movies like Skyfall, The Hangover, Captain America and so much more. The skills behind the camera deserve just as much recognition as the on screen talent and I love that you'll get to hear some of his stories on the show.

22.title: Girl Crush Interview
22.plot: Girl Crush is an American singer and songwriter. Early on in her career, Crush worked with "Cleopatra Records" writing and performing electronic music. In 2012, Crush teamed up with "Blackburner" and their single "Pills" on the "Planet Earth Attack" album went #1 on the international dubstep charts. From there, Girl Crush branched out and made a name as a solo artist on "YouTube" dropping single after single rising to fame. Her most notable singles are "Bow On It" 2013, "Call Me Trouble" ft Lex Lu 2014, "Uh Uh Gurl" 2015, "Play" with "Joy Villa"2015 and a viral cover ...

23.title: Jon Reshard Interview
23.plot: Get to know bassist, producer, and musician Jon Reshard.

24.title: L.T. Hutton Interview
24.plot: This week's interview is with producer, L.T. Hutton; he talks about the making of the new Tupac movie and his purpose and approach with the film.

25.title: Camilla Cleese Interview
25.plot: We have Camilla Chloe Cleese on the show this week.

26.title: Adetokumboh M'Cormack Interview
26.plot: Actor, Adetokumboh M'Cormack (Blood Diamond, Lost, NCIS, Captain America, Battle: Los Angeles) joins us this weekend to talk about how he got into acting. Ade' goes into some very personal stories behind one of his most intense roles, in Blood Diamond, set in Sierra Leone, his hometown. To hear his story and how he has risen to success in acting, is very inspiring. You won't want to miss it.

27.title: Angelo Moore Interview
27.plot: We have Angelo Moore on the show this weekend. Angelo began his career as a famous break dancer in the 80's and soon became the lead singer and creative force behind the legendary band, Fishbone. Fishbone's ability to blend social commentary and humor with a blazing fusion of rock, punk, funk, jazz, ska, reggae, gospel and R&B led to their recognition as one of the most notable acts in American music. After over 25 years in the biz, Moore continues his role as frontman of Fishbone as well as putting out new music with his new band, Angelo Moore and the Brand New Step....

28.title: Lou Ferrigno Jr. Interview
28.plot: Lou Ferrigno Jr. is up next on the show. Check your local cable provider for listings.

29.title: Traci Lords and Peter Stormare Interview
29.plot: This weekend on The Red Booth, we have a chat with Traci Lords and Peter Stormare about their new show Swedish Dicks on Pop TV. Peter plays a Swedish detective in Los Angeles that gets into all kinds of ridiculous trouble. While Traci is the head of a competing detective agency that won't stop giving him a hard time.

30.title: Sadie Katz Interview
30.plot: Get to know scream queen, writer and filmmaker, Sadie Katz. Although she has become known for her roles in scary movies, she's actually an extremely funny person and cracked up our host, Kimberly, quite a few times during this interview.

31.title: Badd Tattoo Interview
31.plot: We have here talented musician duo and brothers, Badd Tattoo. Get to know about their musical journey so far, how they made it from Chicago to LA and lots more.

32.title: Erin Darling Interview
32.plot: This weekend, the gorgeous Erin Darling, is our guest and she talks about a lot of things; from getting into the biz to working with Stan Lee to hosting on major networks, there is a lot we unpack during this interview, so check it out.

33.title: Zack Ward Interview
33.plot: Zack Ward broke onto the scene as a kid playing our favorite bully in the timeless 80's classic "A Christmas Story." He's since continued to act, as well as become a writer and director.

34.title: Dave Yaden 2017 Interview
34.plot: Back on the show is Grammy Winning songwriter and musician, Dave Yaden. Hear about his new album, tips on making money in the music industry and his latest adventures.

35.title: Stelio Savante Interview
35.plot:
Know what this is about?

36.title: Bruce Spaulding Fuller Interview
36.plot: We have the amazing special effects artist Bruce Spaulding Fuller on the show. Bruce has worked on creating monsters in hit films like Predator, Underworld, Terminator 2, Army of Darkness, American Horror Story, Suicide Squad and many more. Get a special peek into this fascinating art form, hear his tips and how he got started.

37.title: Salvador Santana Interview
37.plot: Hostess, Kimberly Q sits down with Salvador Santana, son of the legendary Carlos Santana. They talk about his upcoming album, his new projects to help the Latin community plus what it was like to grow up with music as a way of life.

38.title: Brian A. Metcalf Interview
38.plot: We have on the show this weekend, Brian A. Metcalf, producer on Little Gandhi, which was announced for Oscar Consideration on October 6th, 2017. His new feature film "Living Among Us" is being released by Vision Films in association with Sony Pictures Home Entertainment. We sit down to talk about all of this and more.

39.title: Raz Adoti Interview
39.plot: Get to know actor and director, Razaaq Adoti on the show. He's been in films such as Black Hawk Down, Amistad, Resident Evil and more. We talk about a lot of things, like the new movie he's directing, what it's like working with Ridley Scott and much more.

40.title: The Hollywood Christmas Parade 2017
40.plot: Kimberly Quigley covers the 2017 Hollywood Christmas Parade.

imdb.title: The Red Booth
plot: Classic pinup style TV show hosted and created by Kimberly Quigley. Independently produced, this interview and variety show features up-and-coming and well-known artists.
